```json
{
  "application": "Slurm",
  "details": {
    "nodes": 1,
    "tasks": 1,
    "cores": 64,
    "threads_per_core": 1,
    "partition": "amd",
    "memory": "200G",
    "time": "3000",
    "output_file": "%x-%j.out",
    "modules": "PrgEnv/gcc13-openmpi-python",
    "environment_variables": {
      "PYTHONPATH": "$PYTHONPATH:~/pitts/build_gcc_amd/src/:~/pitts/examples/",
      "PYTHONUNBUFFERED": "1",
      "OMP_STACKSIZE": "100M",
      "LD_PRELOAD": "/scratch/spack-23.2/opt/spack/linux-ubuntu20.04-x86_64_v3/gcc-9.4.0/intel-oneapi-mkl-2023.2.0-sjzhwtp2v6vh5nrppzeijqna3l6cn3ww/mkl/2023.2.0/lib/intel64/libmkl_rt.so:/scratch/spack-23.2/opt/spack/linux-ubuntu20.04-x86_64_v3/gcc-9.4.0/intel-oneapi-mkl-2023.2.0-sjzhwtp2v6vh5nrppzeijqna3l6cn3ww/lib/intel64/libmkl_intel_thread.so:/scratch/spack-23.2/opt/spack/linux-ubuntu20.04-x86_64_v3/gcc-9.4.0/intel-oneapi-mkl-2023.2.0-sjzhwtp2v6vh5nrppzeijqna3l6cn3ww/lib/intel64/libmkl_core.so:$LD_PRELOAD"
    },
    "commands": [
      "srun taskset -c 0-127 likwid-pin -c 0-63 python ttpy_amen.py -n 50 -d 10 --rhs_random_rank  5 --preconditioner=TT-rank1",
      "srun taskset -c 0-127 likwid-pin -c 0-63 python ttpy_amen.py -n 50 -d 10 --rhs_random_rank 10 --preconditioner=TT-rank1",
      "srun taskset -c 0-127 likwid-pin -c 0-63 python ttpy_amen.py -n 50 -d 10 --rhs_random_rank 15 --preconditioner=TT-rank1",
      "srun taskset -c 0-127 likwid-pin -c 0-63 python ttpy_amen.py -n 50 -d 10 --rhs_random_rank 20 --preconditioner=TT-rank1",
      "srun taskset -c 0-127 likwid-pin -c 0-63 python ttpy_amen.py -n 50 -d 10 --rhs_random_rank 25 --preconditioner=TT-rank1",
      "srun taskset -c 0-127 likwid-pin -c 0-63 python ttpy_amen.py -n 50 -d 10 --rhs_random_rank 30 --preconditioner=TT-rank1",
      "srun taskset -c 0-127 likwid-pin -c 0-63 python ttpy_amen.py -n 50 -d 10 --rhs_random_rank 35 --preconditioner=TT-rank1",
      "srun taskset -c 0-127 likwid-pin -c 0-63 python ttpy_amen.py -n 50 -d 10 --rhs_random_rank 40 --preconditioner=TT-rank1",
      "srun taskset -c 0-127 likwid-pin -c 0-63 python ttpy_amen.py -n 50 -d 10 --rhs_random_rank 45 --preconditioner=TT-rank1",
      "srun taskset -c 0-127 likwid-pin -c 0-63 python ttpy_amen.py -n 50 -d 10 --rhs_random_rank 50 --preconditioner=TT-rank1"
    ],
    "software": {
      "python": "ttpy_amen.py",
      "likwid": "likwid-pin"
    }
  }
}
```

This script runs a Slurm job that executes a Python program called `ttpy_amen.py` with various parameters using the `likwid-pin` tool for task pinning. The script also loads a specific environment module and sets up environment variables for Python and the Intel MKL library. The job requests one node, one task, 64 cores, 200GB of memory, and a 3000-second time limit. It runs on the `amd` partition of the Slurm cluster.
